```

## CLI Runner 执行方式

```bash
# 列出所有可用测试
node src/tests/run.mjs

# 运行整个特性模块
node src/tests/run.mjs perps

# 运行子路径
node src/tests/run.mjs settings/language-switch

# 运行单个测试文件
node src/tests/perps/token-search.test.mjs

# 运行特定用例（如脚本支持）
node src/tests/perps/token-search.test.mjs SEARCH-001
```

## Dashboard API

```bash
# 健康检查
curl -s http://localhost:5050/api/status

# 执行指定用例
curl -X POST http://localhost:5050/api/run \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '{"cases": ["SEARCH-001", "SEARCH-002"]}'
```

Dashboard executor (`test-executor.ts`) 通过 `testCases.fn(page)` 或 `mod.run()` 调用。

## ui-map.json 三层选择器策略

```json
{
  "perps-search-input": {
    "primary": "[data-testid=\"perps-search-input\"]",
    "fallback": "input[placeholder*=\"搜索\"]",
    "emergency": "document.querySelector('.search-container input')",
    "description": "合约搜索输入框",
    "lastVerified": "2026-03-23"
  }
}
```

| 层级 | 策略 | 说明 |
|------|------|------|
| primary | `data-testid` | 最稳定，首选 |
| fallback | text/role/placeholder | testid 不可用时 |
| emergency | JS evaluate | 最后手段，通过 `page.evaluate()` |

## QA Director 失败路由逻辑

测试失败后，按根因分类自动路由：

| 根因分类 | 特征 | 路由到 | 处理方式 |
|---------|------|--------|---------|
| `selector_stale` | Element not found, selector timeout | Knowledge Builder | 更新 `ui-map.json` |
| `data_missing` | 余额为 0, Token 未添加 | Knowledge Builder | 更新 `preconditions.json` |
| `assertion_logic` | Expected X got Y, 正则不匹配 | 用户 | 提供代码修改建议（不自己改） |
| `environment` | ECONNREFUSED, Browser closed | 自动 | 重启 OneKey |
| `timing` | 间歇性失败, 加载中点击 | 用户 | 建议加 wait/轮询 |

## Reporter 格式规则

- 耗时格式：`MM:SS`（如 `3:45` = 3 分 45 秒）
- 通过率保留一位小数（如 `80.0%`）
- 失败用例必须附带错误信息摘要
- 有截图的失败用例必须附带截图路径
- 同一天多次运行覆盖同一报告文件
- **永远不删除历史报告**（保留用于趋势分析）

## Do
- Always connect via `chromium.connectOverCDP('http://127.0.0.1:9222')` in Node.js
- Launch OneKey with `--remote-debugging-port=9222` before tests
- Wait ~5s after launch before CDP connect
- Check CDP responds before running tests; if not, pkill + restart
- Use `fn(page)` single parameter for all test functions
- Cache preconditions at module level (`_preReport`) — don't rerun in each fn
- Filter DOM selectors with `.first()` / `.nth()` when multiple matches
- Use position filter `r.y < 100` for top bar selectors to avoid matching other areas
- Use token regex `/^[A-Z][A-Z0-9]{1,9}$/` (tokens can contain digits like XYZ100)
- Treat empty state (no tokens, shows "未找到"/"暂无代币") as valid, not failed
- Take screenshots only on failure — screenshots severely slow down execution
- Keep test scripts as continuous flow (no disconnects mid-test)
- List all recorded actions for user confirmation before generating cases
- Use test ID format `FEATURE-NNN` (e.g., COSMOS-001)
- Restart Dashboard after modifying test scripts (`pkill -f "tsx src/dashboard"` then restart)
- Verify selectors via CDP before adding to `ui-map.json`

## Don't
- Never use any path other than `/Applications/OneKey-3.localized/OneKey.app/Contents/MacOS/OneKey`
- Never use `open` command to launch OneKey or open browser pages
- Never spawn a second OneKey instance (pkill first, then restart)
- Never call `page.setViewportSize()` — use user's current window size
- Never use MCP Playwright tools (browser_navigate, browser_snapshot) for OneKey — it's a separate browser instance
- Never use unconfirmed recordings to generate test cases or update ui-map
- Never modify shared state files outside of the designated writer (see table above)
- Never use deprecated `src/runner/index.mjs` — use `src/tests/run.mjs` instead
- Never use `nativeInputValueSetter` + `dispatchEvent` for React inputs
- Never use `page.keyboard.type()` in CDP Electron — use `locator.pressSequentially()`
- Never use `Meta+a` to clear inputs — triggers Electron global shortcuts
- Never repeatedly click modal trigger elements — check if modal is already open first
- Never use fixed `sleep()` for async results — use polling retry (8-10 attempts × 500ms)
- Never close the browser connection — it's the user's OneKey instance
- Never guess root cause without evidence — collect evidence first
- Never skip precondition checks before test execution
- Bug fixes require user approval — only output diagnosis + repair proposal, don't auto-fix

## Task Status Flow
pending → in_progress → completed | failed | blocked

## Workflow: New Test
Read `shared/knowledge.json` → record (listen.mjs) → user confirms actions → generate .test.mjs + update ui-map + update test_cases.json → if encountered issues, append to knowledge.json

## Workflow: Failure Fix
Read results → classify root cause (5 types) → route to handler → fix → rerun → verify

